pageContext.claim: “It's a conversation with a foreign leader, in this case, a very fine gentleman, president of Ukraine, the new president of Ukraine -- and we call them up and we said, Would it be okay? Our secretary of state made the call, 'Would it be OK?' And they didn't know what we were talking about, but they said, 'Yeah, it's OK.'”
pageContext.analysis: The Ukrainian government thought Trump was only going to release his side of the conversation and was stunned when the full transcript was released.
